author: Source: Daily Herald
title: Rocket with secret payload launches from California coast - Daily Herald
text:
The Atlas V rocket lit up the sky at 5:49 a.m. Thursday, lifting off from Vandenberg Air Force Base toward low-Earth orbit. The rocket carried a payload for the National Reconnaissance Office, which operates the nation's system of intelligence-gathering satellites.
